<li id="cite_note-Stewart-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Stewart_7-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Stewart_7-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFStewart1960" class="citation book cs1">Stewart, John J. (1960). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=yqbtAAAAMAAJ"><i>Mormonism and the Negro</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Wisconsin%E2%80%93Madison" title="University of Wisconsin–Madison">University of Wisconsin–Madison</a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormonism+and+the+Negro&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Wisconsin%E2%80%93Madison&amp;rft.date=1960&amp;rft.aulast=Stewart&amp;rft.aufirst=John+J.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DyqbtAAAAMAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+temple+and+priesthood+policies+in+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/content/manual/teachings-brigham-young/chapter-41">Chapter 41: Temple Ordinances</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Teachings_of_Presidents_of_the_Church:_Brigham_Young" class="mw-redirect" title="Teachings of Presidents of the Church: Brigham Young">Teachings of Presidents of the Church: Brigham Young</a></i> (Salt Lake City, Utah: LDS Church, 1997) p. 299.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Baptism-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Baptism_9-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Baptism_9-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFReiter2017" class="citation journal cs1">Reiter, Tonya (October 2017). "Black Saviors on Mount Zion: Proxy Baptisms and Latter-day Saints of African Descent". <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_of_Mormon_History" class="mw-redirect" title="Journal of Mormon History">Journal of Mormon History</a></i>. <b>43</b> (4). Champaign, Illinois: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>: 100–123. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.5406%2Fjmormhist.43.4.0100">10.5406/jmormhist.43.4.0100</a>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.5406/jmormhist.43.4.0100">10.5406/jmormhist.43.4.0100</a>. <q>Presidents of the Church, with their counselors, consistently gave permission for this level of temple service to be extended to members of African descent, while also forbidding their participation in the endowment ritual. By the mid-1960s, it appears that ... President McKay seems to have agreed that vicarious ordinances should only be done by white proxies, a practice that seems to have been instigated earlier. By the early 1970s, records indicate that black members, once again, had free access to temple fonts in Utah.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Mormon+History&amp;rft.atitle=Black+Saviors+on+Mount+Zion%3A+Proxy+Baptisms+and+Latter-day+Saints+of+African+Descent&amp;rft.volume=43&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=100-123&amp;rft.date=2017-10&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.5406%2Fjmormhist.43.4.0100&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F10.5406%2Fjmormhist.43.4.0100%23id-name%3DJSTOR&amp;rft.aulast=Reiter&amp;rft.aufirst=Tonya&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+temple+and+priesthood+policies+in+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
