<li id="cite_note-Neither_White_Nor_Black-32"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-6"><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-7"><sup><i><b>h</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-8"><sup><i><b>i</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-9"><sup><i><b>j</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-10"><sup><i><b>k</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-11"><sup><i><b>l</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-12"><sup><i><b>m</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-13"><sup><i><b>n</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-14"><sup><i><b>o</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-15"><sup><i><b>p</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-16"><sup><i><b>q</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-17"><sup><i><b>r</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-18"><sup><i><b>s</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_32-19"><sup><i><b>t</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBushMauss1984" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Lester_E._Bush_Jr." title="Lester E. Bush Jr.">Bush, Lester E. Jr.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Armand_L._Mauss" class="mw-redirect" title="Armand L. Mauss">Mauss, Armand L.</a>, eds. (1984). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20221001163611/http://signaturebookslibrary.org/neither-white-nor-black/"><i>Neither White Nor Black: Mormon Scholars Confront the Race Issue in a Universal Church</i></a>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-941214-22-2" title="Special:BookSources/0-941214-22-2"><bdi>0-941214-22-2</bdi></a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/neither-white-nor-black/">the original</a> on October 1, 2022 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Neither+White+Nor+Black%3A+Mormon+Scholars+Confront+the+Race+Issue+in+a+Universal+Church&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1984&amp;rft.isbn=0-941214-22-2&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fsignaturebookslibrary.org%2Fneither-white-nor-black%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+temple+and+priesthood+policies+in+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Turner-33"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Turner_33-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTurner2012" class="citation book cs1">Turner, John G. (September 20, 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=nGgSuTW-dgIC&amp;pg=PA222"><i>Brigham Young: Pioneer Prophet</i></a> (1st&#160;ed.). Cambridge, MA: Belknap Press. p.&#160;222. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-674-04967-3" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-674-04967-3"><bdi>978-0-674-04967-3</bdi></a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">August 28,</span> 2017</span>. <q>If they [the couple and child] were far away from the Gentiles [non-Mormons] they wo[ul]d all have to be killed[.] [W]hen they mingle seed it is death to all. If a black man &amp; white woman come to you &amp; demand baptism can you deny them? [T]he law is their seed shall not be amalg[a]mated. Mulattoes are like mules[,] they can't have the children, but if they will be Eunuchs for the Kingdom of God's Heaven's sake they may have a place in the Temple.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Brigham+Young%3A+Pioneer+Prophet&amp;rft.place=Cambridge%2C+MA&amp;rft.pages=222&amp;rft.edition=1st&amp;rft.pub=Belknap+Press&amp;rft.date=2012-09-20&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-674-04967-3&amp;rft.aulast=Turner&amp;rft.aufirst=John+G.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DnGgSuTW-dgIC%26pg%3DPA222&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+temple+and+priesthood+policies+in+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Collier-34"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Collier_34-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Collier_34-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Collier_34-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCollier1987" class="citation book cs1">Collier, Fred C. (1987). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=LkRZGQ8oO8IC&amp;pg=PA43"><i>The Teachings of President Brigham Young Vol. 3 1852–1854</i></a>. Colliers Publishing Co. p.&#160;43. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-934964-01-7" title="Special:BookSources/0-934964-01-7"><bdi>0-934964-01-7</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Teachings+of+President+Brigham+Young+Vol.+3+1852%E2%80%931854&amp;rft.pages=43&amp;rft.pub=Colliers+Publishing+Co.&amp;rft.date=1987&amp;rft.isbn=0-934964-01-7&amp;rft.aulast=Collier&amp;rft.aufirst=Fred+C.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DLkRZGQ8oO8IC%26pg%3DPA43&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+temple+and+priesthood+policies+in+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
